        <h3><i>"Find & Assist Veterans of Record"</i></h3>
        <p>Return the F.A.V.O.R. (Find & Assist Veterans of Record) is a program for eligible New York State Veterans who have filed their DD-214 with their County Clerk’s Office. If the veteran or family member loses or needs their DD-214, they can return to the Clerk’s office to retrieve a certified copy.</p>

        <p>This program provides veterans with an Individualized Return the FAVOR Identification Card which gives them Discounts on purchases and services at participating merchants. To find out more about how Veterans can file their DD-214 and start accessing the Discounts on this page and in the Discounts Section, please contact your local NYS County Clerk’s Office, Veteran Service Agency or look through our Documents.</p>
